data.value:
Enter the username for an account with administrative privileges to the ArcGIS Server site. This account may be the Primary Site Administrator account entered when the site was first created or an account that has been assigned the administrator privilege within the site.
 
Do not use the operating system account you entered when running the ArcGIS Server setup.

data.value:
Enabling administrative access will allow the ArcGIS Server Manager and Administrator Directory applications to be accessed through the Web Adaptor. When this option is left unchecked (recommended), these applications can continue to be accessed using a direct URL to one of the GIS servers in the site. For example:
 
ArcGIS Server Manager:
https://gisserver.domain.com:6443
/arcgis/manager
 
Administrator Directory:
https://gisserver.domain.com:6443/arcgis/admin
